I have to say, I'm just incredibly impressed by this entry. The setup for all the different iterations is clever (and captures the whole  spirit in the best way), and the execution of the various end-of-the-world tales is just top-notch throughout. The prose is compelling, and each entry does a great job of capturing that feeling of end-of-the-world desperation in a short space (with some especially effective uses of understatement, like the 049 crosslink and the whole Death/2935 section).

I'm sure there'll be some of the traditional complaints about how  but the way this article plays around with the standard format feels anything but arbitrary. Rather, it's a means to the end of telling an effective story, one that wouldn't have quite so memorable of an impact in a more standard format. The ending flash-forward caught me by surprise, but it definitely highlights the themes you referenced in your author post. All in all, an easy +1 from me.







